Please rank, in order of preference, the streams of work you'd like to work on as part of the practicum
property_description:
These streams are described in more detail in the Q&A session we did last month. Here's a brief summary:

*\* Event Classification:* extend the MVP we've built to detect violence and apply it to other types of events (bullying, explicit content, etc.)
*\* MLOps:* Help us operationalize our ML infrastructure with robust pipelines.
*\* Research:* Help us answer some of the fundamental questions about our approach, label reconciliation, weak supervision, etc.

Note that there will be a lot of overlap between these streams (extending the MVP might require you to research new concepts), so these are simply general guidelines about which types of work you're most excited about.

property_description:
This is as surprising to us as it is to you, and we're so sorry! 

We ran into a supply chain block and ordered these units from a different supplier than usual. After doing our own testing, we found out that they aren't "whitelisted" with your carrier like they were supposed to be, in the same way that the phones we normally buy are. 

This means it may not work consistently on Verizon or Verizon MVNOs, and they may not even allow you to activate a SIM card in it. We're taking full responsibility to fix this, and it's our top priority. *You have a few options, which we'll run by you next.*

property_description:
These streams are described in more detail in the Q&A session we did last month. Here's a brief summary:

*\* Extending the MVP:* extend the MVP we've built to detect violence and apply it to other types of events (bullying, explicit content, etc.)
*\* MLOps:* Help us operationalize our ML infrastructure with robust pipelines.
*\* Research:* Help us answer some of the fundamental questions about our approach, label reconciliation, weak supervision, etc.

Note that there will be a lot of overlap between these streams (extending the MVP might require you to research new concepts), so these are simply general guidelines about which types of work you're most excited about.

*We've learned that the pre-owned A32 phone we were going to send you isn't certified on AT&T's network.*
property_description:
This is as surprising to us as it is to you, and we're so sorry! 

We ran into a supply chain block and ordered these units from a different supplier than usual. After doing our own testing, we found out that they aren't "whitelisted" with* *your carrier like they were supposed to be, in the same way that the phones we normally buy are. 

This means it may not work consistently on AT&T or AT&T MVNOs, and they may not even allow you to activate a SIM card in it. We're taking full responsibility to fix this, and it's our top priority. *You have a few options, which we'll run by you next.*
